HEADWORD: Brettice
<hw>Bret"tice</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Brettices</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bretasce</ets>, <ets>bretage</ets>, parapet, OF.
<ets>bretesche</ets> wooden tower, F. <ets>bret⟦egrave⟧che</ets>, LL.
<ets>breteschia</ets>, <ets>bertresca</ets>, prob. fr. OHG.
<ets>bret</ets>, G. <ets>brett</ets> board; akin to E. <ets>board</ets>.
See <er>Board</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, and cf. <er>Bartizan</er>.]</ety>
<def>The wooden boarding used in supporting the roofs and walls of coal
mines. See <er>Brattice</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
